\section{Bridge to the relative cotangent presheaf --- out of autonomous-loop scope}
\label{sec:bridge-out-of-scope}

Theorem~\ref{thm:smooth_locally_free_omega} is stated in the \emph{algebra-K\"ahler form} $\Omega_{\Gamma(X, V) / \Gamma(S, U)}$ for an affine chart $V \subseteq f^{-1}U$, while the relative cotangent presheaf $\Omega_{X/S}$ of Definition~\ref{def:relative_kaehler_presheaf} carries on its section over $V$ the K\"ahler module $\Omega_{\Gamma(X, V) / A_{\mathrm{colim}}}$ over the presheaf-level inverse-image colimit ring $A_{\mathrm{colim}} = (f^{-1}_{\mathrm{psh}}\struct{S})(V) = \mathrm{colim}_{W :\, f V \subseteq W \subseteq S}\,\struct{S}(W)$. The two represent the same mathematical object globally, but on a single affine chart they are connected by a non-trivial $\Gamma(X, V)$-linear isomorphism whose construction requires presheaf-level cofinality machinery. The project keeps both forms (the algebra-K\"ahler form in Theorem~\ref{thm:smooth_locally_free_omega} and the presheaf form in Definition~\ref{def:relative_kaehler_presheaf}) because the bridge is out of autonomous-loop scope.

\begin{remark}[The bridge as a $B$-linear iso between K\"ahler modules]
  \label{rem:bridge_relative_kaehler_iso_appLE}
  Let $f \colon X \to S$ be a morphism of schemes, let $U \subseteq S$ and $V \subseteq X$ be affine opens with $V \leq f^{-1}U$, and write $A := \Gamma(S, U)$, $B := \Gamma(X, V)$, with the appLE algebra structure $A \to B$ induced by $f$. Let $A_{\mathrm{colim}} := (f^{-1}_{\mathrm{psh}}\struct{S})(V) = \mathrm{colim}_{W :\,f V \subseteq W \subseteq U}\,\struct{S}(W)$ denote the presheaf-level inverse-image section ring at $V$. Then there is a canonical $B$-linear isomorphism
  \[
    (\mathrm{relativeDifferentialsPresheaf}\,f).\mathrm{presheaf}(V)
    \;\cong_{B}\;
    \Omega_{B \,/\, A},
  \]
  identifying the section module of the relative cotangent presheaf on $V$ with the appLE-algebra K\"ahler differential module of Theorem~\ref{thm:smooth_locally_free_omega}.
\end{remark}

\emph{Proof sketch} (informational only; the iso is not formalised in Lean this iteration). Under the affine hypotheses, the canonical map $A \to A_{\mathrm{colim}}$ is a localization of $A$ at the multiplicative set
\[
  M \;:=\; \{\, g \in A \,:\, (f.\mathrm{appLE}\,U\,V\,e).\mathrm{hom}\,g \in B^{\times} \,\}
\]
of elements of $A$ that pull back to units in $B$. The argument is: the directed system $\{W \subseteq S : f V \subseteq W\}$ admits a cofinal subsystem of basic opens $D(g) \subseteq U$ with $g \in M$ (these are exactly the affine opens between $f V$ and $U$ on which $g$ becomes a unit after pulling back to $B$, by $V \subseteq f^{-1}D(g)$); for each such $g$, the section ring $\struct{S}(D(g)) = A_{g}$ is the localization of $A$ at $g$ (Mathlib's \texttt{IsAffineOpen.basicOpen\_isLocalization}); and the directed colimit of these localizations over $M$ is the localization $A_{M}$ of $A$ at the full multiplicative set $M$.

Consequently $\Omega_{A_{\mathrm{colim}} / A} = 0$ (the K\"ahler module of a localization is zero, since $\mathrm{d}(g^{-1}) = -g^{-2}\,\mathrm{d}g = 0$ in $\Omega_{A_M/A}$ for every $g \in M$, so the universal derivation is zero). By the second fundamental exact sequence of K\"ahler differentials,
\[
  B \otimes_{A_{\mathrm{colim}}} \Omega_{A_{\mathrm{colim}} / A}
  \;\longrightarrow\; \Omega_{B / A}
  \;\twoheadrightarrow\; \Omega_{B / A_{\mathrm{colim}}}
  \;\longrightarrow\; 0,
\]
the surjection $\Omega_{B / A} \twoheadrightarrow \Omega_{B / A_{\mathrm{colim}}}$ has zero kernel (the kernel is the image of the left term, which is $0$), so it is a $B$-linear iso. Combined with the $\mathrm{rfl}$ identification of Lemma~\ref{lem:relative_kaehler_presheaf_obj}, this gives the claimed iso. The corresponding Mathlib lemma packaging the surjection-with-zero-kernel argument is \texttt{KaehlerDifferential.isLocalizedModule\_map} (\texttt{Mathlib.RingTheory.Etale.Kaehler}).

\emph{Why this iso is out of autonomous-loop scope.} An explicit Lean construction of the iso requires assembling three pieces of off-the-shelf-absent Mathlib infrastructure: (i)~the cofinality of the basic-open subsystem $\{D(g) \subseteq U : g \in M\}$ in the colimit cone $\{W : f V \subseteq W \subseteq S\}$ of \texttt{TopCat.Presheaf.pullback}, (ii)~the identification of the directed colimit of $A_{g}$ for $g \in M$ with the localization $A_{M}$ as a \texttt{CommRingCat} (no Mathlib lemma equates these objects directly at the snapshot \texttt{b80f227}), and (iii)~the resulting algebra-structure compatibility needed to invoke \texttt{KaehlerDifferential.isLocalizedModule\_map}. Estimated cost if a future iteration or downstream user needs this iso: 200--400 lines of Lean. No active project consumer of \texttt{smooth\_locally\_free\_omega} or \texttt{relativeDifferentialsPresheaf} requires the bridge at this iteration; the algebra-K\"ahler form of Theorem~\ref{thm:smooth_locally_free_omega} is sufficient for all downstream uses, and the presheaf form is retained as a leaf object documenting the eventual sheafified $\Omega_{X/S}$ construction.

